00:43:44,648 --> 00:43:46,200
(It's my pleasure to be able to serve)

856
00:43:46,232 --> 00:43:47,490
(Miss and Your Lordship)

857
00:43:47,490 --> 00:43:48,780
(a bowl of mutton noodles.)

858
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:51,640
Ci, have a seat.

859
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:01,864
We once promised we would find
a chance to eat this.

860
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:04,160
Yet, it has dragged on until today.

861
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:06,430
I'm about to leave

862
00:44:07,430 --> 00:44:08,990
and not sure when I will return.

863
00:44:10,030 --> 00:44:10,780
That's great.

864
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:12,950
They are still hot.

865
00:44:14,280 --> 00:44:14,800
Ci,

866
00:44:16,090 --> 00:44:16,680
let's eat.

867
00:44:22,010 --> 00:44:22,840
Ci, are you going

868
00:44:22,840 --> 00:44:24,610
to refuse to eat the noodles with me?

869
00:44:30,340 --> 00:44:31,020
Lord Pei,

870
00:44:31,890 --> 00:44:32,680
give me a moment.

871
00:44:39,970 --> 00:44:41,090
You finally grilled crabs

872
00:44:41,410 --> 00:44:42,680
for me.

873
00:44:43,200 --> 00:44:45,240
You are sincere to me,

874
00:44:45,432 --> 00:44:47,180
I surely have to return it
with my sincerity.

875
00:44:47,760 --> 00:44:49,280
So I grilled some crabs

876
00:44:49,496 --> 00:44:50,950
to thank you for the mutton noodles.

877
00:44:51,496 --> 00:44:52,820
Is there only sincerity between us?

878
00:44:54,200 --> 00:44:55,470
Love is precious

879
00:44:55,672 --> 00:44:57,256
because it's exclusive to someone.

880
00:44:57,704 --> 00:44:59,120
I have had several narrow escapes.

881
00:44:59,544 --> 00:45:00,950
I finally understood my heart.

882
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:02,370
I won't regret

883
00:45:02,870 --> 00:45:03,510
my decision.

884
00:45:04,950 --> 00:45:05,700
Ci,

885
00:45:05,820 --> 00:45:07,840
if it weren't for these incidents,

886
00:45:08,590 --> 00:45:10,870
would you still be by my side?

887
00:45:11,510 --> 00:45:12,990
You belong to the imperial court,

888
00:45:13,430 --> 00:45:14,950
while I belong to the outside world.

889
00:45:15,550 --> 00:45:16,870
It's all predestined

890
00:45:17,120 --> 00:45:18,680
from the beginning.

891
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:21,610
It was me who cut off

892
00:45:21,610 --> 00:45:22,930
the possibility between us.

893
00:45:23,992 --> 00:45:25,990
Still, you have saved me many times.

894
00:45:26,820 --> 00:45:27,870
The three of us

895
00:45:28,640 --> 00:45:30,610
have fought and supported each other

896
00:45:31,424 --> 00:45:33,090
countless times.

897
00:45:33,610 --> 00:45:35,008
I have lost count

898
00:45:35,180 --> 00:45:36,510
as we have come this far.

899
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:38,968
If there's something
that is worth remembering,

900
00:45:39,136 --> 00:45:41,264
it would be the night
the five of us had a drink

901
00:45:41,672 --> 00:45:43,560
at the Lanyue Parlor.

902
00:45:43,736 --> 00:45:44,370
Do you agree?

903
00:45:45,280 --> 00:45:45,840
Cheers.

904
00:45:50,550 --> 00:45:51,620
Let's forget about stances

905
00:45:51,620 --> 00:45:52,610
and grudges.

906
00:45:59,984 --> 00:46:01,470
Ci, you have truly

907
00:46:02,140 --> 00:46:03,680
inspired me.

908
00:46:08,090 --> 00:46:10,090
You said before
that you wished for no wars

909
00:46:10,296 --> 00:46:12,200
and a peaceful and prosperous life
for everyone.

910
00:46:13,090 --> 00:46:13,780
Ci,

911
00:46:15,510 --> 00:46:16,890
I will try everything in my power

912
00:46:17,890 --> 00:46:19,160
to cease this war.

913
00:46:20,510 --> 00:46:21,990
You care for the people and country.

914
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:25,340
Allow me to use these grilled crabs
in place of liquor.

915
00:46:25,870 --> 00:46:27,328
May you return in great victory.

916
00:46:31,090 --> 00:46:31,720
Your Lordship,

917
00:46:32,260 --> 00:46:32,800
please.

918
00:46:34,232 --> 00:46:35,720
I will use the mutton noodles instead.

919
00:46:35,990 --> 00:46:37,640
Ci, please.

920
00:47:08,155 --> 00:47:12,505
♪The slanting sunray refuses to leave♪

921
00:47:12,765 --> 00:47:16,115
♪The moon is fading off♪

922
00:47:17,085 --> 00:47:21,345
♪Frost on the sword, string of the bow♪

923
00:47:21,645 --> 00:47:25,525
♪Bond people together♪

924
00:47:26,095 --> 00:47:30,315
♪The wind heading north and
the wild geese returning from the south♪

925
00:47:30,315 --> 00:47:34,325
♪Who can meet again?♪

926
00:47:34,885 --> 00:47:38,835
♪Looking at the mountains far away
and seeing everything red♪

927
00:47:38,835 --> 00:47:43,075
♪Immersed in the passing years♪

928
00:47:43,305 --> 00:47:47,725
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

929
00:47:47,725 --> 00:47:51,615
♪Yet now I am left wandering
in this life♪

930
00:47:52,185 --> 00:47:56,305
♪Faint memories of the past♪

931
00:47:56,525 --> 00:48:00,375
♪All tell of parting sorrows♪

932
00:48:01,055 --> 00:48:05,295
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

933
00:48:05,535 --> 00:48:09,465
♪Amidst the wind, I suddenly look back♪

934
00:48:09,915 --> 00:48:13,905
♪The face that feels so dear to me♪

935
00:48:14,285 --> 00:48:17,725
♪Where are you now?♪

936
00:48:23,255 --> 00:48:27,645
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

937
00:48:27,645 --> 00:48:31,485
♪Looking back, it seems like a dream♪

938
00:48:32,005 --> 00:48:36,255
♪Don't forget each other
even if we're far apart♪

939
00:48:36,635 --> 00:48:40,315
♪Don't waste time♪

940
00:48:41,005 --> 00:48:45,195
♪Back then, the road seemed ordinary♪

941
00:48:45,465 --> 00:48:49,335
♪Taste all the vicissitudes of life
in a flash♪

942
00:48:49,945 --> 00:48:54,085
♪Though nothing is permanent♪

943
00:48:54,665 --> 00:48:58,115
♪I wish you well♪
